## Checklist for a new API resource

- [ ] **Scope**: Resource is standard Laravel (app/) or inside a **module** (Modules/{ModuleName}/) — use correct paths and namespaces (`Modules\{ModuleName}\...`).
- [ ] Route: `Route::apiResource(...)` in `routes/api.php` (standard) or `Modules/{ModuleName}/routes/api.php` (module).
- [ ] Controller in `App\Http\Controllers\API` or `Modules\{ModuleName}\Http\Controllers\API`, Service injected, index uses FilterRequest + `Model::getQuery()->paginate()`, store/update use Data + Service
- [ ] `App\Data\{Model}Data` with HasModelAttributes, `$model`, validation attributes
- [ ] Form Request (store/update) and FilterRequest in `{Model}Requests\`
- [ ] Service with `store`/`update` and `DB::transaction`
- [ ] Policy with AuthorizesByPermissionGroup and view/create/update/delete
- [ ] Permissions seeder + PermissionGroup enum case
- [ ] Filter trait with getQuery(), allowedFilters, allowedSorts, scopes; model uses trait
- [ ] API Resource with toArray (camelCase)
- [ ] Factory; Pest tests in `tests/Feature/{Model}/` using ResponseMessages and factories
